<p>Consider an experiment. In it, the effect of Social Stress (Factor with two groups: <span class="math inline">\(z_{1}\)</span>) on Performance (Dependent variable: <span class="math inline">\(y\)</span> ) is studied. The researchers used a standard ANCOVA, controlling for Neuroticism (Covariate: <span class="math inline">\(x\)</span>, with <span class="math inline">\(\bar{x} = 20\)</span>). The following estimated regression equation is found: <span class="math inline">\(\hat{y}=25+0.8_{x}+2z_{1}\)</span>. Calculate the adjusted means for both groups of the Factor.</p>
</p>]]></text>
